          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- Abstract: the E1 Amplitude of the Transition to the",
                "Ground State in the 12C(A,GAMMA)16O Capture Reaction",
                "Was Measured in the Energy Range E-Cm=1.3 to 3.0 MeV",
                "Using an Intense 12-C Beam in Combination with a",
                "Windowless 4-He Gas Target and an Array of Six 70% Hpge",
                "Detectors.   The Detectors were Placed in a Ring-Shaped",
                "Geometry Around the Target, at a Distance of 17 Cm on a",
                "Plane  Perpendicular to the Beam Axis.  A Target Length",
                "Of 5.3 Cm was Defined by a 12.5 Cm Thick Lead",
                "Shielding.  Passive and Active Shielding was Used to",
                "Achieve the Necessary Suppression of the Beam Induced",
                "And Cosmic Background.  The Results of this Measurement",
                "And Their Extrapolation to the Relevant Energy During",
                "The Helium Burning Phase in Massive Stars are Reported."
              ]
            }
          ],
